            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/component\/10071",
                    "id": 10071,
                    "name": "Zend_Currency",
                    "description": "Zend_Currency is a Class which handles all Currency related functions and is locale aware.",
                    "isAssigneeTypeValid": false
                }
            ]
        },
        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41209",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as non-issue.\r\n\r\nAccording to the manual and the API setValue() accepts:\r\n* integer\r\n* float\r\n* Zend_Currency\r\n\r\nA localized string is no valid input. When you want to give a localized string as value then you need to normalize it before or extend Zend_Currency to do this.\r\n\r\nReason: \"value\" is internally a float.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-27T07:57:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-27T07:57:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41221",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "name": "psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Przemyslaw Sobczuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that it shoud be dependet from locale settings at all.\r\n\r\nKeep on mind that showing currency is with locale settings:\r\nin pl_PL locale\r\n $curr->setValue('123.45'); \/\/value must be set with dot, I can't set value with comma\r\necho $curr; \/\/ 123,45 - always print comma = correct for Poland\r\n\r\nIt's illogical.\r\n\r\nValue should be set directly (without changes) from forms.\r\n\r\nNotice. Numeric keyborad (right side of keyboard) in polish standard has got comma insted of dot. It's default for us. Writing float numbers with dot is problematic.\r\n\r\n\"Value\" should be internally a float, as is.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "name": "psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Przemyslaw Sobczuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-28T00:24:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-28T00:24:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41456",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Again:\r\nA string is not accepted as input. You need to make a float.\r\n\r\nYou can set it from within a form... add a filter.\r\n\r\nAlso your notice is not logical... when you use a polish keyboard we can also expect that your environment locale is polish which means that PHP itself does the conversion for you. When not: Add a filter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-13T13:23:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-13T13:23:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "name": "psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Przemyslaw Sobczuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You are right that I can use filter. It can solve my problem but it is one more thing to remember while creating form. As well I can use str_replace(',','.',$str);\r\n\r\nAll incoming data from forms are strings.\r\nFloat numbers contains comma insted of dot.\r\nSimple conversion done by the Zend_Currency ($val = floatval( $val );) gives me only an integer part of that string.\r\n\r\nAs you said I can use filters, but it would be more convenient if the class did it automatically based on Zend_Locale.\r\n\r\nIf you think I am wrong you can close this ticket.\r\n\r\nThanks for taking the time.\r\n\r\nps\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "name": "psobczuk@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Przemyslaw Sobczuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-14T01:36:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-14T01:36:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41462",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ianmonge",
                        "name": "ianmonge",
                        "displayName": "Ian Monge",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can use this:\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\n$filter = new Zend_Filter_LocalizedToNormalized();\r\n$filter->filter('53,95);\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nIt returns a string:\r\n\r\n53.95\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ianmonge",
                        "name": "ianmonge",
                        "displayName": "Ian Monge",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-14T04:12:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-14T04:12:35.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
